((date 2026-06-30) (slug tiebreak-noise-floor)
 (hypothesis
  "Diagnostic (user-requested): add 3 UNINFORMATIVE control tiebreaks -- Reverse_alphabetical, Symbol_length, Hash_order (FNV-1a pseudo-random) -- as default-off candidate_ranking modes, and grid them vs the Alphabetical baseline on top-500/top-1000 PIT-1998 2000-2026 13-fold Cell-E long-only. They carry no return signal, so they bracket the NOISE FLOOR of the equal-score tiebreak. If the informative sorts (RS-primary Quality #1788, earliness-primary Quality_earliness) sit INSIDE the band the controls span, no sort beats unbiased sampling.")
 (base_scenario "GRID 2-cell breadth x {baseline, reverse_alpha, symbol_length, hash_random(FNV)}, 2000-2026, 13 folds. baseline reproduces #1788 bit-for-bit.")
 (window_id grid-2cell-breadth-wfcv-2000-2026-13fold-2y)
 (baseline_label baseline)
 (variants
  (;; --- top-500: Sharpe band 0.609..0.682 (width ~0.073); all tiebreaks within ---
   ((label top500-alphabetical) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.667) (mean_calmar 0.850) (mean_return_pct 17.80) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 14.79)))))
   ((label top500-symbol_length) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.682) (mean_calmar 0.676) (mean_return_pct 18.27) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 16.21)))))
   ((label top500-hash_fnv) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.640) (mean_calmar 0.762) (mean_return_pct 16.33) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 14.52)))))
   ((label top500-reverse_alpha) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.609) (mean_calmar 0.661) (mean_return_pct 15.08) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 15.24)))))
   ;; --- top-1000: Sharpe band 0.388..0.666 (width ~0.278); flips winner vs top-500 ---
   ((label top1000-alphabetical) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.660) (mean_calmar 0.690) (mean_return_pct 18.68) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 17.29)))))
   ((label top1000-reverse_alpha) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.589) (mean_calmar 0.574) (mean_return_pct 15.49) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 16.07)))))
   ((label top1000-symbol_length) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.422) (mean_calmar 0.478) (mean_return_pct 11.44) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 17.83)))))
   ((label top1000-hash_fnv) (config_hash "") (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.388) (mean_calmar 0.405) (mean_return_pct 9.61) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 17.22)))))))
 (verdict Reject)
 (notes
  "DIAGNOSTIC noise-floor experiment (not a promotion candidate); verdict Reject = no tiebreak (informative OR arbitrary) is promotable, keep Alphabetical default. THREE findings: (1) NO informative sort escapes the noise band -- RS-primary (#1788: t500 0.636 / t1000 0.666) and earliness (t500 0.649 / t1000 0.590) both sit INSIDE the spread the arbitrary controls span, in both cells; they do not beat the best arbitrary sort. Confirms project_edge_is_the_fat_tail / accuracy_is_unreachable: no entry-feature sort adds return. (2) the 'best' arbitrary tiebreak FLIPS by cell -- Symbol_length best in top-500 (0.682, even > alphabetical 0.667) but COLLAPSES in top-1000 (0.422); Alphabetical/RS best in top-1000. A ticker's name/length is causally irrelevant, so a sort that wins one cell and loses the next is drawing from a distribution, not exploiting an edge -> alphabetical being 'best' in prior broad backtests is partly LUCK-of-the-draw on a single path, not a reliable property. (3) the tiebreak is a LARGE, breadth-scaling source of pure selection VARIANCE: arbitrary-sort Sharpe spread widens 0.073 (top-500) -> 0.278 (top-1000) as over-subscription doubles (~5 fundable slots vs many tied grade-A breakouts). IMPLICATIONS: candidate-ranking lever is dead (keep Alphabetical, unbiased not good); broad single-tiebreak backtests carry hidden +-0.07..0.28 Sharpe selection variance (lean on WF-CV fold distributions, not single-window points); the productive direction is to REDUCE the variance (fund more names / smaller positions = the concentration/capacity axis project_capacity_concentration_surface, a tail-preserving lever) NOT re-sort, and the per-screen decision-audit (dev/plans/per-screen-decision-audit-2026-06-30.md) to see which picks drive the spread. BUG-FOUND: first Hash_order used h*31+byte = monotonic in length -> bit-identical to Symbol_length; caught before conclusions, fixed to 32-bit FNV-1a (XOR-first diffuses). Artifacts: dev/experiments/tiebreak-noise-floor-2026-06-30/ (FINDINGS.md + out_top{500,1000}{,_hashfix}). top-3000 controls not run (would widen the band further; future confirmation)."))
